(Eventually, it became obvious that researchers had grossly underestimated the difficulty of) Tj
T* (the project. In 1974, in response to the criticism from James Lighthill and ongoing pressure) Tj
T* (from Congress, the governments of the United States and the United Kingdom stopped) Tj
T* (funding undirected research into artificial intelligence. Seven years later, a visionary) Tj
T* (initiative by the Japanese Government inspired governments and industry to provide AI) Tj
T* (with billions of dollars, but by the late 1980s the investors became disillusioned and) Tj
T* (withdrew funding again.) Tj
